General Assembly Raised Bill No. 152
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 1204
Referred to Committee on HOUSING
Introduced by:
(HSG)
AN ACT APPROPRIATING FUNDS FOR RENTAL ASSISTANCE
PROGRAM HOUSING INSPECTIONS.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 Section 1. (Effective July 1, 2026) The sum of two hundred fifty
2 thousand dollars is appropriated to the Department of Housing from
3 the General Fund, for the fiscal year ending June 30, 2027, for
4 administration of the rental assistance program established in sections
5 8-345 to 8-346a, inclusive, of the general statutes, for purposes of hiring
6 additional full-time staff to inspect compliance of housing units with
7 state and local health, housing, building and safety codes pursuant to
8 subsection (b) of section 8-345 of the general statutes.
This act shall take effect as follows and shall amend the following
sections:
Section 1 July 1, 2026 New section
